article.headline: Air Force 71, Texas-Pan American 50
article.story: AIR FORCE ACADEMY, Colo. -- Andrew Henke matched his career high with 23 points Saturday as Air Force defeated Texas-Pan American 71-50 in the Falcons' fourth straight win. Air Force (7-2) never trailed and led 40-26 at halftime. The Falcons used a 17-8 run to open the second half and led 57-34 with 11:21 left to play. The Broncs (3-7) couldn't get closer than 18 points after that. The Falcons benefited from 52 percent shooting from the field and 9-of-18 shooting from 3-point range. Texas-Pan American finished the game shooting 37.5 percent from the field. Emmanuel Jones had 15 points and six rebounds to lead Texas-Pan American.
